%^RESET%^%^CYAN%^The following classes are available:%^RESET%^

    Barbarian
    Bard
    Cleric
    Druid
    Fighter
    Mage
    Monk
    Paladin
    Psion
    Psywarrior
    Ranger
    Sorcerer
    Thief
    Warlock


Each class has its own strengths and weaknesses, represented by a unique set of feats and abilities.  Some classes are restricted based on race, alignment and/or stats.  For information about each class, see %^BOLD%^%^WHITE%^<help CLASS>%^RESET%^.

%^BOLD%^%^CYAN%^Multi-classing:%^RESET%^
When you advance beyond level 10, 20, 30 and 40 you will be given the option to %^CYAN%^multi-class%^RESET%^.  To do so, simply type %^BOLD%^%^WHITE%^<advance NEW_CLASS>%^RESET%^ in an area that allows advancement and you will become a %^CYAN%^"multi-classed character"%^RESET%^.  When you reach the new bracket, you may choose to advance in your new or old class or even pick up a third.  Some classes have multi-class restrictions noted in their help-files.  Note that you must meet the requirements of any class that you decide to pick up.

%^BOLD%^%^CYAN%^Prestige Classes:%^RESET%^
Additionally, when you advance past level 40 you may pick up a %^CYAN%^prestige class%^RESET%^.  These offer specialized and often more powerful abilities, but they come with a small range of prerequisites.  For more information on these, see %^BOLD%^%^WHITE%^<help prestige classes>%^RESET%^. 

%^CYAN%^See also: %^RESET%^ advance, stats, feats, races, alignments.
